<span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="no">RSpec</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="no">Matchers</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="no">BuiltIn</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="no">Eq</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mh">0x00007ff85e0678c8</span> <span class="vi">@expected</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'foo'</span><span class="o">&gt;</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>=&gt; eq(resultat attendu) renvoit un objet BuiltIn::Eq du module ::Matchers</p>

<p>Les √©l√©ments qui composent les assertions sont donc de simples objets ruby</p>

